\section{Shared options and constants}

The watcher redraws the terminal, the public-exposure flow prints a fixed
warning, and several commands share the same configuration-backed defaults.
Keeping the user-facing strings here makes the help text consistent and exposes
the relevant configuration keys wherever users look for them.

The configuration command needs the full list of supported keys, while its help
text should expose the short names people actually type at the terminal.  We
derive the help text from the same tuple so adding a setting cannot leave the
configuration help stale.

