The statistic callouts share one low-level formatter.  It builds Rich
[[Text]] directly rather than parsing markup strings, so option labels that
look like terminal style markup are still shown literally.

<<functions>>=
def _stats_line(pairs: list[tuple[str, str]]) -> Text:
    line = Text()
    for index, (label, value) in enumerate(pairs):
        if index:
            line.append(" | ")
        line.append(f"{label}: ", style="dim")
        line.append(value, style="bold")
    return line
@

The multiple-choice callout mirrors the HTML mode chip.  It deliberately reads
the modal option and percentage from the same summary fields as the web page,
so terminal and browser views cannot disagree about the highlighted answer.

<<functions>>=
def _render_terminal_mc_stats(
    question: dict,
    summary: dict,
    *,
    console: Console,
):
    mode_index = summary.get("mode_index")
    if mode_index is None:
        return
    label = str(question["options"][mode_index])
    percentage = summary["percentages"][mode_index]
    line = _stats_line([("Mode", label)])
    line.append(f" ({percentage:.0f}%)")
    console.print(line)
@

